    "abstract": "<jats:title>ABSTRACT</jats:title>\n                <jats:p>\n                  Coronaviruses can cause severe respiratory infections in humans. In this study we assessed the antiviral activity of Pacific oyster (\n                  <jats:italic>Crassostrea gigas</jats:italic>\n                  ) hemolymph against a human coronavirus, HCoV-229E. An eight-fold reduction in infectivity of HCoV-229E on Huh-7 cells was observed in the presence of 10%\n                  <jats:italic>C. gigas</jats:italic>\n                  hemolymph. Antiviral activity of\n                  <jats:italic>C. gigas</jats:italic>\n                  hemolymph positively correlated with its concentration and appears to be active during an intracellular stage of HCoV-229E infection.\n                </jats:p>",
    "DOI": "10.1101/2021.11.01.466695",
